description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Nuclear Medicine Technologist/Radiographer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for experienced Nuclear Medicine Technologists/Radiographers to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department is spread across three sites; Charing Cross Hospital, St Mary’s Hospital and Hammersmith Hospital. The successful candidates will participate in the three site rotation that is in operation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The trust wide PET/CT service is based at Charing Cross Hospital, where there is a Siemens Biograph 64 scanner. We have a busy PET/CT service, which includes 18F-FDG, 68Ga-Dotatate, 68Ga-PSMA, 18F-Choline, 18F-Florbetaben (NeuraceqTM) studies and numerous research studies using a variety of isotopes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SPECT CT Imaging is available at Hammersmith and St Mary’s Hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first ever Symbia Intervo Bold systems have been installed in the newly refurbished department at Hammersmith Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alongside the growing SPECT/CT service a wide range of examinations and therapies are undertaken including Myocardial Perfusion Imaging, DAT scans, general NM studies, 177Lutetium, thyroid, SIRTeX and Therasphere therapies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We also run a trust wide and external GFR sample processing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;St Mary Hospital delivers our paediatric nuclear medicine service using a GE Infinia SPECT/CT and a single headed Siemens ECAM.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a flexible approach to working hours to meet the needs of the individual and the service. Please talk to us at interview about the flexibility you may need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contact Luis Alves, PET/CT Modality Lead Technologist on 020 331 30595 or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joy Murrell, Nuclear Medicine Modality Lead Radiographer 020 331 34732 for further information and/or to arrange a visit to any of the departments.&lt;/p&gt;
